Class YAMLParser.YMLNode

java.lang.Object
YAMLParser.YAMLParser.YMLNode
Enclosing class:
YAMLParser
public static class YAMLParser.YMLNode
extends java.lang.Object
A yml node contains either a value or children. The node also contains an id.
Author:
jonas.franz

  • Constructor Details

    • YMLNode

      public YMLNode​(java.util.List<Token> tokens, int depth) throws MalformedYMLException
      Parses a YML-Node from the given token stream. This call may be recursive, and build the YML-Subtree defined in the token stream.
      Parameters:
      tokens - The Tokens that represent the YML-File.
      depth - The current parsing depth, or indentation depth for this node.
      Throws:
      MalformedYMLException - Thrown if the YML-Input does not follow YML-Conventions.

  • Method Details

    • countIndent

      private int countIndent​(java.util.List<Token> tokens)
      Counts the amount of indentation-tokens that are back to back from the start of the list.
      Parameters:
      tokens - The list containing the tokens.
      Returns:
      The amount of indentation tokens.

    • accept

      protected static Token accept​(java.util.List<Token> tokens, Token.TokenType type) throws MalformedYMLException
      Checks if the first token type is the given type. If this is the case, the first token is removed from the list and returned.
      Parameters:
      tokens - The token list.
      type - The expected type of the first token.
      Returns:
      The removed first token.
      Throws:
      MalformedYMLException - Thrown if the list is empty or the token type is not equal to the expected.

    • accept

      private YAMLParser.YMLNode getNodeRec​(java.lang.String ID)

    • getValue

      public java.lang.String getValue​(java.lang.String ID)
      Returns the value of the node with given ID. If this node has the given ID, the value of this node is returned. Otherwise, the subtree of this node is searched for the given ID.
      Parameters:
      ID - The ID of the searched node.
      Returns:
      The value that was found or null if no node exists with the given id.
